lessons.theory:
## Defining Functions

```rust
// Parameters MUST have types
fn add(a: i32, b: i32) -> i32 {
    a + b // No semicolon means return this value!
}

// Or explicit return
fn multiply(a: i32, b: i32) -> i32 {
    return a * b;
}
```

Notice how omitting the semicolon at the end of an expression implicitly returns it.

