lessons.theory:
## Borrowing data
Instead of taking ownership (or cloning, which is slow), we can **borrow** data using references (`&`).

```rust
fn calculate_length(s: &String) -> usize {
    s.len() // We have a reference, we don't own it
}

fn main() {
    let s1 = String::from("hello");
    let len = calculate_length(&s1); // Pass a reference
    // s1 is still valid here!
}
```

